args: They've broken through our ranks on the\nright side! Shepherds, move to the center\nand shift to defensive formation!
Stand tall. This is the decisive moment.
We can't fall here... Not when the future\nwe've dreamed of is so close!
Leave the front gate to us, Captain.\nYou go tend to the others!
...Heh. You've grown into quite the\ndependable bunch.
Very well. I'll leave things here to you.\nSee that you return alive!
Thórr! Your will has gone unchallenged\nlong enough!
You have quite the penchant for resisting\nfate, O prince of Ylisse.

But it makes no difference in the end.
This world has already been judged.
There is not a soul here worthy of
becoming a heavenly hero.
Now, feel the power of my divine hammer!
This is but an omen—a prelude to this\nworld's inevitable destruction.
Prepare yourselves. It will be upon\nyou soon.
Rrgh... DAMN HER!\nI need to check on the others...
Save your strength. I'll bring Zethia\nright away.
Hah... It's too late for that, Captain.\nJust let me...tell you what happened.
Everything outside...just a diversion...\nThórr came here, and her power...it was...
All our training...was nothing against\na god... All we did...was for nothing.
I promise, everything you did was for a\npurpose.
Heh... Thanks, Captain. You really are...\na beacon of hope...
Did no one else survive?\nI'm here! Say something!
So long as you draw breath, Zethia can\nheal you! I'll take you to her myself!\nANSWER ME!
So this is the power of the gods...
...No. I can't give in to grief.
I need to find Zethia. I won't let this flame\ngo out!
Chrom, I... I have a favor to ask...
*cough* Please, don't trouble yourself.\nI know my time is running out.
We have a way to save this world now.\nI need you to take it back in time.
Go to the past, and prevent this future \nof despair from ever coming to fruition.
It's so quiet. Thórr's forces must\nhave withdrawn when there was\nno one left...
I couldn't find a single survivor.
I'm so sorry, everyone... I let all of\nyou down when it mattered most.
But I've no time to wallow in self pity.\nI need to use the power Princess Zethia\ngave me to travel back through time and—
Thórr! Have you come to stop me?\nYou will not find it a simple task!
Lower your blade, mortal. I am not here\nfor battle.
I come with a question: Now that\njudgment has been dealt to this\nworld, what will you do?
You and your allies clung to hope despite\nknowing the future you sought may never\nbe.

In the end, you failed to overcome my
trial—but you need not feel ashamed.
I witnessed the souls of true warriors
this day. You have earned my respect.
And so I would learn your intent,\nas this world's sole survivor.
You will embark for the past, I take it?\nTo a time when this world's present was\nbut one of many futures.
Yes... Despite knowing your efforts may\nbe in vain, you do not waver. You truly\nare the epitome of humanity's strength.
If that strength one day lifts your will\nabove that of the gods, this trial will\nhave been well worth it.
Perhaps you are the one who will meet\nmy expectations and defy the ruinous fate\ndecreed by my master.
I don't select my actions to please you\nor any god that aims to toy with our lives!
The people of this world were strong of\nspirit, and fought with dignity and bravery.
I won't let their efforts be in vain! I refuse\nto surrender to your claims of ＂fate＂!
I will journey to the past and see their\ndreams realized!
I see. Then show me just how strong\nhumanity can be.
I'll show you all that and more!
I'll prove that fate is not absolute!
Very well. I shall bear witness to your\ndeeds.
Show me the strength of your spirits,\nwarriors of the dragonblood realm.
Present Day\nShadow Ruins: Before the Sealed Door
(I'm sorry, Zethia. But I can't just hand\nover your solution to him.)
(I've traveled here to realize the dreams\nof everyone in that world.)
(So it is my duty to lay low any who\nmight threaten them, now or in the future.)
Let me judge whether you are worthy of\nbearing the fate of this world.
Show me the strength of your convictions,\nPrince {player_name}!
